<p>GDP growth: 3.9% GDP: $25bn (PPP: $54bn) Inflation: 7.3% Population: 10.4m GDP per head: $2,440 (PPP: $5,210)</p>

<p>The Movimiento al Socialismo government under leftist president Evo Morales has a large majority in the legislature, but is losing the people. Even with the tailwinds provided by revenue from exports of natural gas, living standards are falling far short of expectations. Violent protest and ineffective government and doses of martial law will prevent development outside the natural-resources sector.</p>

